The new coat of pale green paint looks like a sickly covering of undercoat, I really believed it was an undercoat until I asked.

What a shock!

MG

Participant

I saw that on Saturday. What a horrible colour, what were they thinking. It the colour of mint toothpaste.

Anonymous

Participant

yep its awful alright, i saw the undercoat which was a creamy kind of colour and looked very well i cant believe they put that muck over it , who decides these things??

Anonymous

Participant

dunno about you, but it reminds me of my mum’s garden trellis….

ooh, they should weave ivy and roses thru it – eh?

Anonymous

Participant

Why is it that they always seem to get it wrong.Grattan Bridge looks yucky now.A great example of colour blindness.What a colour combination insipid green and black. This bridge could have been better painted with a more suitable colour. With it’s detailing; the sea horses and ornate lamps makes it a perfect canvas.

Mind you, the blue and white job further down the Liffey looks quite attractive.Too bad about the surrounding quayside areas.Will they please sort out this mess.Give Bargaintown & Co a kick in the arse to ammend their business premises appearances.

Anonymous

Participant

Also will they please give the loop-line bridge a coat of fresh paint.It would do wonders.

Rory W

Participant

Ah, but take a look at it when it is lit up at night!!!!
